Finally, we combine these results using `gcongr`. The goal at this point is to show:
`eLpNorm (T' g₁) 1 (ν.restrict G) + eLpNorm (T' g₂) 1 (ν.restrict G) + eLpNorm (T' g₃) 1 (ν.restrict G) + eLpNorm (T' g₄) 1 (ν.restrict G) ≤ (4 * c / p) * eLorentzNorm (g₁ • C + ... ) p 1 μ * (ν G) ^ p'⁻¹.toReal`.

The `gcongr` tactic splits this into four goals, each corresponding to one term. We provide the corresponding hypothesis (`h1`, `h2`, etc.) to solve each goal.

```tactics
